               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 7ra-24va)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 24vb-50rc)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     50va-140rb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 50va-60ra)
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 60vb-63vb), preceded by an excerpt
                     from “The Book of the Testament” (fol. 60ra-vb)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our
                     Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 63vc-74rc)
 III-4) Anaphora of St
                     John, son of Thunder (fols. 74va-83ra)
 III-5) Anaphora of St John
                     Chrysostom (fols. 83ra-88rc)
 III-6) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus
                     (fols. 88va-95ra)
 III-7) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea
                     (fols. 95ra-103va)
 III-8) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols.
                     103va-109vb)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols.
                     109vb-112vb)
 III-10) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols.
                     112vc-121vb)
 III-11) Anaphora of St Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy of St
                     Gregory”) (fols. 121vb-126va)
 III-12) Second Anaphora of St Gregory
                     (“Christmas-liturgy of St Gregory”) (fols. 126va-128vb)
 III-13) Anaphora
                     of St Basil of Caesarea (fols. 128vb-135rb)
 III-14) Anaphora of St Cyril
                     of Alexandria (fols. 135rb-140rb)
 
 Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>ff. 2-5 are of considerably smaller size than the rest of the folios.
                        They have probably been appended to S<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqmm008">QMM-008</ref>at a later stage. The folios contain the hymn Śarāwita
                        malāʾǝktihu la-Madḫāne ʿĀlam “The hosts of the angels of the Saviour of the
                        world” written out for various liturgical occasions.</note>
                     <note>Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (text III-10) is not inscribed
                        with the saint’s name.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
