                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the ruling King, Patriarch
                           and Metropolitan; incipits and headings of the constituent texts;
                           directives for the ministers; part of the musical notation signs above
                           the lines; most of the abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs
                           and Ethiopic numbers.
 
 The incipits or incipit pages of most of
                           the constituent texts are written alternately in red and black lines (s.
                           fols. 7ra-rc, 24vb-vc, 50va-vc, 74va-vc, etc.).</seg>
