                     <origDate notBefore="1777" notAfter="1779">
                        <locus target="#23rb">23rb-</locus>rc, 44rb: Sälomon is mentioned as the
                        ruling king. <locus target="#34vc">34vc</locus>: Ṗeṭros is mentioned as the
                        Patriarch and ʾIyosab as the Metropolitan. <locus target="#50vb">50vb</locus>: Yoḥannǝs is mentioned as “our bishop”. Sälomon II was the
                        king of Ethiopia in 1777-79; Sälomon III was the king of Ethiopia in 1796-97
                        and in 1799. ʾIyosab II was the metropolitan of Ethiopia in 1770-1803. John
                        XVIII was the patriarch of Alexandria in 1769-96. The name of Ṗeṭros as the
                        Alexandrian patriarch is mentioned for unclear reasons.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>The donor’s name in supplication formulas has
